from referring to it as a ``terrorist state'' after a meeting with
that country's ambassador.
   Jackson met Ambassador Pieter Koornhof for an hour Wednesday to
ask for the protection of three men who sought protection at the
U.S. Consulate in Johannesburg.
   The three men in South Africa had been jailed without trial for
as long as 21 months and entered the consulate Tuesday after
escaping from their guards at a hospital.
   Before the meeting took place, though, the South African
government already said the three anti-apartheid leaders would not
be rearrested if they left the consulate.
