hellos with one and all but never took handouts. More than $1,400
has been raised toward installation of a bench and permanent plaque
in his honor.
   ``There was a certain pride in Malibu Joe that isn't typical
with the usual street people,'' said Malibu Times editor Gil
Peters. ``For some reason, he turned himself into a folk hero.''
