<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Abandoned Boy,0179</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hearing-Impaired Boy Found Abandoned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GALLUP, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hearing-impaired boy who apparently cannot
speak was abandoned in a church playground by a woman who then
disappeared, police say.
   The 3- or 4-year-old boy was found Saturday after an anonymous
caller said she saw a woman leave the boy that afternoon in the
playground of the First Methodist Church.
   ``He appeared to be well taken care of,'' Detective Tony Sanchez
said Wednesday. ``He can make noises but nothing understandable.''
   Officers are calling the boy David Gallup and have placed him in
state Social Services custody.
   ``I don't think he's from around here because we would have
heard something from someone by now,'' Sanchez said.
   Doctors said the boy's developmental level seemed low but that
might be attributable to his hearing impairment and apparent
inability to communicate, Sanchez said.
   His case seemed similar to that of a hearing impaired boy found
wandering the streets of Ciudad Juarez, Mexico, earlier this year.
That child eventually was reunited with his mother in Mexico.
</TEXT>
