<1ST_LINE>r a AM-APColumbusAppointments     09-15 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-AP Columbus Appointments,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Columbus Asst. Bureau Chief, News Editor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dale Leach, news editor for The Associated
Press in Columbus, has been named assistant chief of bureau for the
news cooperative in Ohio.
   Keith Robinson, an AP newsman in Columbus, has been named to
succeed Leach as news editor. The appointments were announced
Thursday by Columbus Chief of Bureau Jake Booher.
   Leach, 36, has been news editor in Columbus since 1984. He
joined the AP as a newsman here in 1981 after working for the
Beavercreek Daily News in Dayton and the Sprinfield (Ohio) News-Sun.
   Leach is a native of Springfield and a graduate of Ohio State
University. He succeeds Terry Kinney, who recently was named AP's
chief of bureau in Charleston, W.Va.
   Robinson, 36, is a Philadelphia native who graduated from
Indiana University of Pennsylvania. He began his journalism career
at The Madison Press in London, Ohio, and joined the AP in Columbus
in 1984.
</TEXT>
