<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Sicily-Tornado     09-15 0128</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sicily-Tornado,0131</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tornado Injures 35</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COMISO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tornado roared through this town outside
the U.S. cruise missile base in southeastern Sicily on Thursday and
injured at least 35 people, officials said.
   The twister damaged many buildings and cars, felled trees and
antennas, tore down signs and hurled blocks of marble dozens of
yards. It also caused some damage in Ragusa, 10 miles east of
Comiso. There were no reports of damage at the missile base.
   Comiso Mayor Salvatore Zago immediately asked for help from
civil defense and that the town be declared a disaster area to make
it eligible for relief funds.
   Officials said 10 people were hospitalized, including two in
serious condition, and that 25 others were treated and released for
minor injuries.
</TEXT>
