<HEAD>Three Killed In Helicopter Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A helicopter burst into flames and
crashed for an unknown reason, killing three of the four people
aboard, the government daily Magyar Hirlap said Thursday.
   The accident occurred Wednesday while the helicopter was on a
mission in Badacsonytordemic, about 75 miles southwest of Budapest,
the newspaper said.
   Magyar Hirlap identified the victims as police Maj. Bela Kiss,
39, Sandor Szabo, 56 and Istan Varga, 59. It said the fourth person
aboard suffered slight injuries.
   Authorities of the military prosecution office and the
ministries of interior and defense launched an investigation into
the cause of the crash, the newspaper said.
</TEXT>
