<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan announced Thursday he is
nominating Ferdinand F. Fernandez to be a federal appellate judge
on the 9th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in California.
   Reagan made the announcement to representatives of Hispanic news
media gathered in an auditorium of the Old Executive Office
Building next to the White House.
   Fernandez, 51, if confirmed by the Senate, would succeed Warren
J. Ferguson.
   Since 1985, Fernandez has served as a federal district judge for
the Central District of California. Before that, he was a judge for
the Superior Court of the state of California in San Bernardino
County in 1980-85.
   Fernandez graduated from the University of Southern California
in 1958 and the University of Southern California Law School four
years later. He lives in Upland, Calif.
