<HEAD>Wife Of Douglas Fairbanks Jr. Dies Of Cancer At 75</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mary Lee Fairbanks, second wife of actor
Douglas Fairbanks Jr., has died of cancer. She was 75.
   Mrs. Fairbanks married the actor a few months after meeting him
at a New Year's Eve party in 1939.
   ``She was a girl absolutely full of enthusiasm, excitement and
laughter,'' said Herb Swope, who had invited her to the party.
``She had a humorous view of life. She was always in good humor.''
   Fairbanks, 78, was married twice, first to Joan Crawford,
1929-1934, and then to Mary Lee in 1939.
   The marriage was also Mrs. Fairbank's second _ her first was to
A&P supermarket heir Huntington Hartford.
   Aside from her work with Hospice in Palm Beach County, Mrs.
Fairbanks lived quietly at her home here. She died Wednesday at
Good Samaritan Hospital in neighboring West Palm Beach.
   Besides her husband, survivors include daughters Daphne
Fairbanks, Victoria Fairbanks and Melissa Morant; and eight
grandchildren.
   Funeral services were scheduled Saturday.
