<HEAD>Actor Tom Berenger Doesn't Mind Being Bad</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: For release 6 p.m. EDT</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Tom Berenger, who has played a maniacal
slasher in ``Looking for Mr. Goodbar'' and a racist in
``Betrayed,'' says he enjoys playing the bad guy.
   ``I find something human in them, with the exception of `Mr.
Goodbar,''' Berenger told US magazine in its Oct. 3 issue. ``It was
such a slimy character with no redeeming qualities. To me it was
like playing Charles Manson. I had nightmares after I finished
shooting. I felt dirty.''
   Yet when working on a role, Berenger says, he doesn't think
about his character's bad nature. ``You can't think that you're
playing a villain or you'll end up with a cartoon.''
   Berenger recently completed a script about an Irish rebellion
and included a part in it for him: ``the bad guy. Or, at least, the
insensitive one.''
</TEXT>
