<HEAD>Ethiopian Jetliner Crash-lands, No Deaths Reported</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Ethiopian Airlines jetliner with
104 people aboard crash-landed Thursday at Bahar Dar airport, and
an undetermined number of people were injured, the Ethiopian
television reported.
   The state-owned TV did not report any deaths from the 12:45 a.m
(5:45 a.m. EDT) crash-landing of the Boeing 737.
   The jetliner was on a domestic flight from Addis Ababa to the
Red Sea port of Asmara with a stopover at Bahar Dar, 186 miles
north of the capital, Addis Ababa.
   The cause of the accident was not reported.
   The TV station said those injured were flown to the hospital in
Asmara, 248 miles to the north, and also to Addis Ababa. The report
did not indicate the nature of the injuries, whether the aircraft
sustained damage or the nationalities of those aboard.
   Bahar Dar is in northwestern Ethiopia at the shores of Lake
Tana, the source of the Blue Nile, and the picturesque region is
frequented by tourists.
