<1ST_LINE>a e PM-APonTV-WoodyandLeadbelly Adv16   09-15 0868</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-AP on TV-Woody and Leadbelly, Adv 16,0881</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>$Adv16</NOTE>
<NOTE>For Release Fri PMs, Sept. 16, and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>Tribute to Woody Guthrie and Leadbelly on Showtime</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   There's something kind of poignant about
watching wealthy rock stars pay homage to those two monumental
influences, Woody Guthrie and Leadbelly, both of whom died
basically penniless. But at least they know who they owe.
with the just-released album, Showtime has produced
an inspired video tribute to the folk legends, featuring
performances by and interviews with Bruce Springsteen, U2, Pete
Seeger, Arlo Guthrie, Little Richard and John Cougar Mellencamp,   To
go along 
among others.
   ``The All-Star Tribute to Woody Guthrie and Leadbelly''
premieres Saturday with additional playdates Sept. 20, 26, 30 and
Oct. 9 and 11. Robbie Robertson is the narrator. The success of the
film was probably never in doubt since it comes from director Jim
Brown and producer Harold Leventhal, the team responsible for the
Emmy-winning 1982 documentary, ``The Weavers: Wasn't That a Time.''
   Though it was Bob Dylan's idea that spawned the CBS record,
``Folkways: A Vision Shared,'' and therefore the Showtime special,
he doesn't appear on camera. But, against a backdrop of old still
photographs that show how much Dylan tried to emulate Woody
Guthrie, down to the cigarette hanging from his lip, he talkis has been
using against Bush in recent campaign appearances.
   ``Michael Dukakis balanced 10 budgets in a row and still cut
taxes five times,'' the announcer in the 30-second
``Responsibility'' ad says.
   The ad also refers to the rate of personal income growth in
Massachusetts, which is twice the national average, and the
governor's successful effort to win passage of the first state law
guaranteeing health insurance to virtually all workers.
   ``That's why America's governors, both Democrat and Republican,
voted Michael Dukakis the most effective governor in the nation,''
the announcer says.
   Dukakis campaign aides declined to say how much the campaign was
spending on the new round of ads, to be supplemented by a new
commerical paid for by the Democratic National Committee.
   The naming of John Hancock's David D'Allesandro to head the
Dukakis ad team was characterized by several Dukakis aides as a key
move in an effort to bring more direction to advertising strategy.
   The move was orchestrated by John Sasso, the Dukakis confidant
who recently returned as vice chairman of the Democratic campaign,
said Dukakis media adviser Francis O'Brien.
</TEXT>
