<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
231,477 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
189,579, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
when 208,787 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 144,708 cars this week,
compared with 119,535 a week ago and 131,202 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 86,769,
compared with last week's 70,044 and last year's 77,585.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,581 cars this week, up from
16,251 a week ago and from last year's 15,692.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,563,
compared with 17,089 a week ago and 10,413 in the same week last
year.
