<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Obit-Kiernan     09-15 0212</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Kiernan,0228</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fleet@Norstar Chairman Peter Kiernan Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peter D. Kiernan, the chairman and chief
executive officer of Fleet@Norstar Financial Group has died as a
result of complications from emergency surgery he underwent last
month.
   Kiernan, 65, died Wednesday in the intensive care unit of the
Massachusetts General Hospital in Boston, where he had been
transferred following surgery to remove an aneurysm in his aorta.
   Kiernan fell ill while vacationing at his family's summer home
on Cape Cod Aug. 18 and underwent surgery at Falmouth Hospital, in
Falmouth, Mass.
   J. Terrence Murray, Fleet@Norstar's president and chief
operating officer, called Kiernan ``a source of inspiration and
leadership for this corporation and the entire banking industry.''
   Kiernan became chairman and chief executive of Fleet@Norstar
Jan. 1, 1988 upon completion of the merger berween Fleet Financial
Group, of Providence, and the Albany-based Norstar Bancorp.
   As part of the merger agreement, Kiernan was scheduled to retire
Dec. 31, with Murray assuming his titles.
   Kiernan, an Albany native, lived with his family in Newtonville,
N.Y.
   Kiernan was elected vice chairman of Norstar Bancorp in 1973,
president and chief executive officer in 1974, and chairman in 1975.
   Fleet@Norstar is a $25-billion diversified national financial
services company. It has about 1,000 offices in 40 states.
</TEXT>
