16]. Ames said it agreed to buy Zayre's 388-unit discount store
division in a deal it valued at about $800 million.
   Other major retailing issues showed little effect from the
August sales report. Sears Roebuck was down [ at 36{; J.C. Penney
dropped | to 48[, and K mart was unchanged at 36[.
   Macmillan Inc. climbed 2 to 86{. Maxwell Communication Corp.
raised its bid for the company, which has agreed to a buyout by an
investor group for $85 a share.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market lost $9.27 billion, or 0.35
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
dropped .53 to 151.60.
   Standard & Poor's industrial index fell 1.45 to 307.94, and
S&P's 500-stock composite index was down 1.18 at 268.13.
   The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market
slumped 1.15 to 382.70. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index closed at 297.70, down .65.
